text: The Law Society of Newfoundland Labrador founded in 1834 (as Newfoundland Law Society and current name in 1999) is the statutory body charged with the regulation of the legal profession in the Canadian province of Newfoundland and Labrador. ==References== Newfoundland and Labrador Category:Lawyers in Newfoundland and Labrador Category:Newfoundland and Labrador law Category:1834 establishments in the British Empire Category:Organizations established in 1834
title: Law Society of Newfoundland and Labrador
